INSERT INTO `wp_comments` VALUES (434,85,'Smack','technologyedition9+2@gmail.com','','115.115.82.210','2012-10-29 17:30:34','2012-10-29 12:00:34','Its really nice. I\'m also looking to buy similar one...',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:15.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/15.0.1','',0,79),(435,204,'RoyaltweetDotCom','cklless@gmail.com','','210.187.202.113','2012-11-23 05:55:41','2012-11-23 00:25:41','Is the a way to make pictures view in a light box?',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (iPad; CPU OS 6_0_1 like Mac OS X) AppleWebKit/536.26 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/6.0 Mobile/10A523 Safari/8536.25','',0,131),(436,204,'shaaz369','shahzad.saeed@rtcamp.com','','115.115.82.210','2012-12-01 14:37:41','2012-12-01 09:07:41','See this end user guide for more help\r\nhttp://rtcamp.com/buddypress-media/user-guide/',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.91 Safari/537.11','',0,2),(437,204,'VK','vegaskev88@gmail.com','','70.189.210.248','2012-12-18 11:01:16','2012-12-18 05:31:16','Loving this plugin.  Might I throw 2 suggestions?\r\n\r\n1.)  When uploading a single photo it does not give me a chance to choose which album...it just assumes that I want it in the \"Wall Posts\" album.  I tested this after I created an additional album and got the same results.  Can you please mod the code to support \"choose album\" even when only one photo is uploaded?\r\n\r\n2.)  When a photo is in an album, there is no way to move it to a different album if a user later decides to move it to a different album.  Is there a way to add a \"move to different album\" option?\r\n\r\nAlso, what is the \"featured\" button for under a photo?  just curious.  So glad I found your plugin.  If we can choose album for single upload, it will be a godsend.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.97 Safari/537.11','',0,291),(438,204,'admin','admin@rtcamp.com','','106.76.247.163','2012-12-19 22:36:17','2012-12-19 17:06:17','Hi VK,\r\n\r\nThank you for the suggestions. Would you be kind enough and add this to our <a href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/buddypress-media/issues?state=open\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">github issues list</a> or our <a href=\"https://rtcamp.com/support/forum/buddypress-media/feature-requests/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">support forum</a>. This comment form is just meant for testing the functionality. We do not monitor comments here except for spam and such monitoring does not include support or feature requests.\r\n\r\nThis time both of us were lucky. We\'d have easily missed this.\r\n\r\nRegards.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Linux x86_64) AppleWebKit/537.11 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/23.0.1271.97 Safari/537.11','',0,1),(442,204,'admin','admin@rtcamp.com','','115.115.82.210','2013-03-01 17:46:50','2013-03-01 12:16:50','Light box will be added in BuddyPress-media core as soon sa BuddyPress 1.7 will be out.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.22 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/25.0.1364.99 Safari/537.22','',435,1),(443,668,'admin','admin@rtcamp.com','','115.115.82.210','2013-03-21 13:43:02','2013-03-21 08:13:02','sdadasd',0,'post-trashed','Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_8_2) AppleWebKit/537.22 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/25.0.1364.172 Safari/537.22','',0,1);
