downloads. We have been constantly getting user feedback, criticism, appreciation and suggestions. Considering user demands and current technologyÂ trends we decided to do some major changes in rtPanel Framework to make it more quality oriented and to enhance the user experience.</p>\n<h3>Quick WordPress Approval:</h3>\n<p>Surprisingly rtPanel version 2.1 is approved in less than 10 hours by WordPress theme review team as there were no errors reported. Now, the new version is available for users to <a title=\"Download rtPanel\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/rtpanel/download/\">download</a>.Â <span style=\"text-align: center;\">Â </span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/rtPanel2.jpg\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-8011\" title=\"rtPanel Released\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/rtPanel2-600x530.jpg\" alt=\"rtPanel Released\" width=\"206\" height=\"182\" /></a></p>\n<p>Below are the changes in this major release:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>New Look:</strong> The default design has been improved with more polished look, better icons and styles.</li>\n<li><strong>960gs: </strong>The new version is developed over 960 grid system. It will ensure the better visibility and control in all screen resolutions</li>\n<li><strong>HTML5 and CSS3</strong>: We are following the technology trends and hence now new release will support HTML5 and CSS3 toÂ make it more browser friendly and light.The framework should be minimal and hence we have removed some non-essential CSS files and made the framework more robust; with cleaner CSS. Now overriding of parent CSS in child themes would be easier.</li>\n<li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong>Â This release is also a responsive design, which will support (render equally good) iPad, iPod, iPhone, Android, tabs and BlackBerry Mobile Devices.</li>\n<li><strong>bbPress Support</strong>: Unlike old version, new version will have the bbPress support as well. It means that rtPanel users can have forums on their site.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The new version has already been approved by WordPress and is available to <a title=\"Download rtPanel\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/rtpanel/download/\">download</a>. You can also <a title=\"Fork rtPanel on GitHub\" href=\"http://github.com/rtcamp/rtpanel\">fork it on GitHub</a> and see the latest development.</p>\n<p>Please note that as its a major release; CSS may break since we moved to HTML5 markup and added 960gs grid support. If youÂ face any difficulty, please feel free to contact our <a title=\"rtPanel Support\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/\">Support Forum</a>, we would always be there to answer your concerns.</p>\n<p>We will soon release a small version for WordPress 3.4 features&#8217; support. So stay tuned. <img src=\'http://rtcamp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p><strong>Important Links:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a title=\"Support Forum\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/rtpanel/download/\">rtPanel 2.1 Download</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Support Forum\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/\">Support Forum</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Fork it on GitHub\" href=\"https://github.com/rtcamp/rtpanel\">Fork it on GitHub</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"ChangeLog\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/rtpanel/changelog/\">ChangeLog</a></li>\n</ul>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/EW7EtlEpHyU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"http://rtcamp.com/news/rtpanel-new-release-2-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"http://rtcamp.com/news/rtpanel-new-release-2-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"Fix rtPanel Child Theme For rtPanel-2.1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/HHCMhH9VCBk/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/fix-rtpanel-child-theme-for-rtpanel-2-1/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 12 Jun 2012 08:13:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://rtcamp.com/?p=7936\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:184:\"We have recently released the major version of rtPanel, with loads of changes in markup and use of 960 gs; to make rtPanel more user friendly and inline with current technology trends.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Gajanan Sapate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3378:\"<p>Hello Friends.</p>\n<p>We have recently released the major version of rtPanel, with loads of changes in markup and use of 960 gs; to make rtPanel more user friendly and inline with current technology trends.</p>\n<p>Fortunately WordPress 3.4 has also been released with rtPanel 2.1, hence we immediately did some fixes to ensure, themes will not break with WordPress 3.4 and launched a one more minor revision as rtPanel 2.1.1</p>\n<p>Change is always difficult to adopt, and we do understand that many rtPanel users across the globe must be facing problems of broken child theme with recent updates.</p>\n<p>However, as promised, we are here to offer free technical support to rtPanel developers on our <a title=\"Support Forums\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/\">support forums</a>. For now, you can follow the below fix to fix the major issues.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Fixing Broken Theme:</h2>\n<p>To avoid the major CSS issues, you need to place the following codeÂ after &#8220;@import url (&#8220;../rtpanel/style.css&#8221;);&#8221;Â in your rtPanel child theme&#8217;s Style.css file:</p>\n<p><code> /* rtPanel Upgrade Script Styles */<br />\nbody { line-height: 150%; }<br />\n.post-title { float: none; }<br />\n#header { margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; }<br />\n#rtp-primary-menu { background: none; }<br />\n#rtp-primary-menu, #rtp-nav-menu ul, #rtp-nav-menu ul li a { border: 0; }<br />\n#main-wrapper { margin: 0 auto; }<br />\n.post-content p { margin-bottom: 24px; }<br />\np { line-height: inherit; margin: 0; }<br />\n.post-content, .widget, #respond form, select, input, textarea, button { font-family: \"HelveticaNeue-Light\", \"Helvetica Neue Light\", \"Helvetica Neue\", Helvetica, Arial, \"Lucida Grande\", sans-serif }<br />\nh1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 { line-height:136.4%; font-family: inherit; }<br />\n#content { float: left; }<br />\n#sidebar { float: right; }<br />\n.widget { line-height: 153.9%; margin-top: 0; }<br />\n#footerbar { overflow: hidden; }<br />\n.widget .widgettitle { margin: 0; }<br />\n.rtp-single-post img, .rtp-singular img { max-width: 100%; }<br />\n.rtp-single-post .post-content a, .rtp-singular .post-content a { text-decoration: none; }<br />\n.post-content img.alignnone { margin: 10px 10px 10px 0; }<br />\nimg { -moz-box-sizing: inherit; -webkit-box-sizing: inherit; box-sizing: inherit; }<br />\n/* site specific */<br />\n.post-content img.alignleft { margin: 2px 13px 5px 0; }<br />\n/*<br />\nIf following classes have been used in your theme to target post images then you need to adjust the styling with the following classes<br />\npost-img-left =&gt; img.alignleft<br />\npost-img-right =&gt; img.alignright<br />\npost-img-none =&gt; img.alingnone<br />\npost-img-center =&gt; img.aligncenter<br />\n*/<br />\n/* Remove Comments Count */<br />\nfunction rtp_remove_parent_hooks() {<br />\nremove_action( \'rtp_hook_end_post_title\', \'rtp_default_comment_count\');<br />\n}<br />\nadd_action( \'init\', \'rtp_remove_parent_hooks\' );<br />\n</code></p>\n<p>Above code will fix major problems; you might still face some issue, if you have applied custom styles to your themes. Feel free to ask your questions on our <a title=\"Support Forum\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/\">support forum</a>, we will be happy to assist you further.</p>\n<p>Cheers!!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/HHCMhH9VCBk\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/fix-rtpanel-child-theme-for-rtpanel-2-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/fix-rtpanel-child-theme-for-rtpanel-2-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Assign Custom Metabox To Specific Page Template\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/QXxK99j2woA/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/assign-custom-metabox-to-specific-page-template/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 18 Apr 2012 11:57:57 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Case Study\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://rtpanel.com/?p=2360\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:329:\"Custom meta-boxes allows you to add piece of custom data to posts or pages. In one of our previous post we have seen about how easy it is to deploy custom metabox using rtPanel Child Theme. The rtp-custom-metaboxes.php present in the rtPanel Child Theme has the basic function that is required to deploy the meta box in the site.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Apeksha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2882:\"<p>Custom meta-boxes allows you to add piece of custom data to posts or pages. In one of our <a title=\"Creating Metabox\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/creating-metabox/\">previous post</a> we have seen about how easy it is to deploy custom metaboxÂ using rtPanel Child Theme. The <strong>rtp-custom-metaboxes.phpÂ </strong>present in theÂ rtPanel Child Theme has the basic function that is required to deploy the meta box in the site.</p>\n<p>The meta box can be implemented in the Â post/ page editor of specific page template at the WordPressÂ back-end.</p>\n<p>Example: Refer the below screenshot, which contains certain page sections which are displayed from MetaBoxes.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/metaboxes.png\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"aligncenter size-full  wp-image-5041\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/metaboxes.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"760\" height=\"558\" /></a></p>\n<p>In above screenshot you can notice that Â on Home page template, different page sections like &#8216;Slogan&#8217; and &#8216;content boxes&#8217; are displayed using custom metaboxes functionality. These are manged from page editors at WordPress back end. Â Please refer the below screenshot to see the back-end:</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/metaboxes_backend.png\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-2421\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/metaboxes_backend-600x386.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"386\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Â Assigning Metaboxes to the page templates:</h3>\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Create a page template (For details refer <a href=\"http://rtpanel.com/blog/creating-custom-page-templates-rtpanel-child-theme/\" target=\"_blank\">this</a> ).</p>\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Replace code present in the rtp_post_types_custom_box() with the following oneÂ  :</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">global $post;\n $template_file = get_post_meta( $post-&gt;ID, \'_wp_page_template\', TRUE );\n if ( $template_file == \'featured-template.php\' ) {\n add_meta_box ( \'post_custom_field_id\', __( \'Custom Field\', \'rtPanel\' ), \'rtp_posts_inner_custom_box\', \'page\', \'side\', \'high\' );\n }</code></pre>\n<p>Here in above code, meta boxes are linked to &#8220;featured-template.php&#8221;. You can replace the template name with the one you have created for whichÂ Â meta boxÂ will be displayed.</p>\n<p>This is useful when we are applying the meta box value only to one page or to page having some specific page template.</p>\n<p>For any questions about using metboxes in rtPanel, please contact on our <a title=\"Support Forum\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/forum/developer/\">Support Forums</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/QXxK99j2woA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/assign-custom-metabox-to-specific-page-template/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/assign-custom-metabox-to-specific-page-template/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Create Custom Theme Options To Add Header Image\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/BUS_hE6N92k/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/create-custom-theme-options-to-add-header-image/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 09 Apr 2012 14:07:11 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Case Study\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://rtpanel.com/?p=2111\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:290:\"Many times, client demands to have a control over the website look and hence the they want the header image to be managed with easy option. The best way to do that is to provide a theme option to manage the header image. Have a look at below screenshot for the sample. Adding Image to [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Apeksha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3714:\"<p>Many times, client demands to have a control over the website look and hence the they want the header image to be managed with easy option. The best way to do that is to provide a theme option to manage the header image. Have a look at below screenshot for the sample. <a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/HeaderImage_custom-theme-options.png\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"aligncenter size-full  wp-image-5044\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/HeaderImage_custom-theme-options.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"609\" height=\"561\" /></a></p>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3>Adding Image to Header From Custom Theme Options:</h3>\n<p>rtPanel is pre-equipped with all the basic functionality required. Creating a theme option to add images to header is very simple and it can be achieved with three easy steps as below:</p>\n<h4>1. Get code from rtp-custom-theme-options.php:</h4>\n<p>rtPanel child theme contains pre-defined theme option file as &#8216;rtp-custom-theme-options.php&#8217; in lib folder of child theme. You can see the codes on Github <a title=\"rtPanel Child theme\" href=\"https://github.com/rtCamp/rtpanel-child-theme\">here</a>. Â ItÂ has âImage Uploaderâ field by default so we don&#8217;t have to write extra codes in this page.</p>\n<h4>2. Create Function at functions.php:</h4>\n<p>All we need to do is toÂ create a function in functions.php file and then add the code to display image from rtp-custom-theme-options.php file in that function. The function with code will look as below:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">&lt;?php function rtp_display_img(){\n global $rtp_custom_theme_options;&lt;?php $custom_image_uploader = wp_get_attachment_image_src( @$rtp_custom_theme_options[\'custom_image_id\'], \'thumbnail\' ); ?&gt;Â  Â &lt;img src=\"&lt;?php echo @$custom_image_uploader[0] ?&gt;\" alt=\"Custom Image\"&lt;?php echo ( isset( $custom_image_uploader[0] ) ?Â  \'style=\"max-width: 240px; width: 100%;\"\' : \'style=\"max-width: 240px; width: 100%; display: none;\"\' ); ?&gt; /&gt; &lt;?php } ?&gt;</code></pre>\n<p>This is how it looks at the backend in the admin area of Custom Theme Options page. <a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/photos-rtparty2011-rtcamps-second-anniversary-celebration/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-2112\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2112\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/customthemeoptions3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"968\" height=\"269\" /></a>The code has default styling for the image which is displayed. You can also add CSS style to the image in the desired way you would like to display it.</p>\n<h4>3. Add Hook:</h4>\n<p>Once we have created the function we have to hook it. As we have to display this image Â after header we will use &#8216;rtp_hook_after_header&#8217;. For example,</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">add_action(\'rtp_hook_after_header\',\'rtp_display_img\');</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>Â <span style=\"line-height: 21px\">Â </span><span style=\"line-height: 21px\">By default the image will be displayed above the menu as theÂ </span>menu in the site uses same hook with the priority <strong>10</strong>.Â If you would like to display the image below the menu then you have to set the priority more than 10. For Example,</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">add_action(\'rtp_hook_after_header\',\'rtp_display_img\',12);</code></pre>\n<p>I hope above tutorial was helpful. You may ask your questions below as comments or on our <a title=\"Support Forum\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/support/forum/rtpanel/forum/developer/\">support forums</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/BUS_hE6N92k\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/create-custom-theme-options-to-add-header-image/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"3\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/create-custom-theme-options-to-add-header-image/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"Customizing Image Sliders in rtPanel Child Theme\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/LvJjHiOn2NE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/customizing-image-sliders-in-rtpanel-child-theme/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 04 Apr 2012 14:14:50 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://rtpanel.com/?p=2243\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:157:\"The image slider enhances the beauty of the website. The image slider can be used to showcase the product or to display the portfolio or featured blog posts.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Apeksha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3896:\"<p>The image slider enhances the beauty of the website. The image slider can be used to showcase the product or to display the portfolio or featured blog posts.</p>\n<p><span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">In the earlierÂ </span><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/implementing-rtpslider-child-theme/\" target=\"_blank\">post</a> <span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">we have seen how easy it is, to add the slider in your website using rtPanel child theme. By default this slider will display latest 10 posts&#8217; featured image with its post title and the excerpt.Â </span><span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">Through this post we will show few more examples about how the slider can be presented in different ways:</span></p>\n<h3>1. Displaying only images:</h3>\n<p>By default the slider displaysÂ latest 10 posts featured image with its post title and the excerpt. If you would like to display only images on the post then you need to comment the following line in the code:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">Â  $slider_html .= \'&lt;h1&gt;&lt;a href=\"\' . get_permalink() .\'\" title=\"\'. Â get_the_title().\'\" rel=\"bookmark\" &gt;\' . ( ( strlen( get_the_title() ) &gt; 50 ) ? substr( get_the_title(), 0, 50 ) . \"...\" : get_the_title() ) . \'&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;\' .\'&lt;h6&gt;\'. get_the_excerpt().\'&lt;/h6&gt;\';</code></pre>\n<h3>2. Displaying the images from the posts of specific categories:</h3>\n<p>In many of our projects we have displayed slider where the post belonged to specific category. Â For example, posts having &#8216;Slider&#8217; category will only be displayed on the slider. Â To display such post in the slider you just need to add the category name in the the<strong><em>Â rtp-slideshow.phpÂ </em></strong><span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">F</span>or example, if you want to display the posts of &#8216;Slider&#8217; category on the slider then you just need to addÂ <strong>Â &#8217;category_name&#8217; =&gt;&#8217;slider&#8217;</strong> in below code</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">Â query_posts( array( \'ignore_sticky_posts\' =&gt; 1, \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 10, \'order\' =&gt; \'DESC\') );</code></pre>\n<p>Thus the code will be as below:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">Â query_posts( array( \'ignore_sticky_posts\' =&gt; 1, \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 10, \'order\' =&gt; \'DESC\', \'category_name\' =&gt;\'slider\') );</code></pre>\n<h3>3. Displaying the image from the page attachment:</h3>\n<p>The images which are attached to the page can be displayed in the slider. That is, each page will display its page attachment in the Slider. Â For this you have to replace the code in theÂ rtp_get_cycle_slider() function with below code:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">global $post;\n $images = &amp; get_children( array( \'post_type\' =&gt; \'attachment\', \'post_mime_type\' =&gt; \'image\', \'order\' =&gt; \'ASC\', \'post_parent\' =&gt; $post-&gt;ID, \'numberposts\' =&gt; 20 ) );\n $slider_html = \'\';\n if ( count( $images ) &gt; 1 ) {\n $slider_html .= \'&lt;div class=\"clear\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=\"rtp-cycle-slider\"&gt;&lt;div class=\"rtp-cycle-slider-container\"&gt;\';\n foreach ( $images as $image ) {\n $slider_html .= \'&lt;div class=\"cycle-slides\"&gt;\' . wp_get_attachment_image( $image-&gt;ID, \'rtp-slider\' ) . \'&lt;/div&gt;\';\n }\n $slider_html .= \'&lt;/div&gt;\';\n }\n echo $slider_html;</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The slider will beÂ <span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">only</span><span style=\"line-height: 21px;\">Â </span>display if there are minimum 2 images in the page attachment.</p>\n<p>Thus using rtPanel child theme deploying the slider in the website becomes easy and presenting it in diffrent way is much easier. You can add your CSS styling to the class in the div tags to enhance the slider design. <img src=\'http://rtcamp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/LvJjHiOn2NE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/customizing-image-sliders-in-rtpanel-child-theme/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/customizing-image-sliders-in-rtpanel-child-theme/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"Display Image Signature Below Post Content\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/TqS4MmqspkE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/display-image-signature-below-post-content/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sat, 31 Mar 2012 11:29:34 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Case Study\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://rtpanel.com/?p=2161\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:243:\"In this post we will see about one more hook i.e \"rtp_hook_end_post_content\" It is used to hook the function after the post content. For example, this hook can be used to display the signature (image of the signature) after every post content.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Apeksha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3545:\"<p>In the <a title=\"rtPanel Hooks\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/hooks-rtpanel-child-theme/\">previous post</a> we have seen about few hooks in the rtPanel and also read that how can we use such hooks in our website. In this post we will see about one more hook i.e &#8220;rtp_hook_end_post_content&#8221; It is used to hook the function after the post content. For example, this hook can be used to display the signature (image of the signature) after every post content.</p>\n<h3>Example: Display custom signature image at end of post content on single posts.</h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Signature_rtPanel.png\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"size-full  aligncenter wp-image-5047\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/Signature_rtPanel.png\" alt=\"rtPanel Hooks\" width=\"472\" height=\"638\" /></a></p>\n<p>So lets see step-by-step guide for its implementation.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Â In the &#8220;functions.php&#8221; file, create a custom function and write the code to display the image. For example,</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">function custom_hook_end_post() {\n echo \'&lt;img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/mylogo.jpg&gt;\"&gt;\';\n}</code></pre>\n<p>If you want to display the image from the custom uploader which is present in the Custom Theme Options you have to write the below code:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">function custom_hook_end_post() {\n global $rtp_custom_theme_options;\n $custom_image_uploader = wp_get_attachment_image_src( @$rtp_custom_theme_options[\'custom_image_id\'], \'thumbnail\' );\n  echo \'&lt;img src=\"\'.@$custom_image_uploader[0].\'\"&gt;\';\n}</code></pre>\n<p>This function will display the image after ever page/post content.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 2:</strong>Â If you want to display the image only on particular page the you have to add some condition in the code, such as:</p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>Â if( is_page() ) Â </strong>To display image only on page (not on the post page).</p>\n<p><strong>if(is_single())</strong> Â To display image only on pageÂ single post page.</p>\n<p><strong>if(is_singular()) </strong>To display image onÂ page and single post page.</p></blockquote>\n<p>For example,</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">function custom_hook_end_post() {\n global $rtp_custom_theme_options;\n $custom_image_uploader = wp_get_attachment_image_src( @$rtp_custom_theme_options[\'custom_image_id\'], \'thumbnail\' );\n if( is_page() )\n echo \'&lt;img src=\"\'.@$custom_image_uploader[0].\'\" class=\"rtp_after_post_img\"&gt;\';\n}</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Once you have created the function you have to hook it using add action. For which you have to add the below:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">add_action( \'rtp_hook_end_post_content\', \'custom_hook_end_post\' );</code></pre>\n<p>and you are done. After this the image will be displayed below the page/post content as given in above image.</p>\n<p>There can be many other usage of &#8216;rtp_hook_end_post_content&#8217; hook, based on your creative approach. One more reference example can be using this hook to to display the social networking icons or Â social networkingÂ plugins. <img src=\'http://rtcamp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>Related Post: <a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/hooks-rtpanel-child-theme/\">Adding Google ad banner above logo in rtPanel child theme.</a></p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/TqS4MmqspkE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/display-image-signature-below-post-content/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"http://rtcamp.com/case-study/display-image-signature-below-post-content/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"Add Google ad-banner above logo in rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/rtpanel/~3/BsfmDiyjnlY/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/add-google-ad-banner-above-logo-in-rtpanel/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 30 Mar 2012 10:14:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"rtPanel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"http://rtpanel.com/?p=2303\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:151:\"In previous post, we have seen the rtPanel Hooks map. Now lets see how we can we use \'rtPanel Hooks\' to add extra functionality while developing theme.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Gajanan Sapate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3004:\"<p>In <a title=\"rtPanel Hooks Map\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/hooks-rtpanel-child-theme/\">previous post</a>, we have seen the rtPanel Hooks map. Now lets see how we can we use &#8216;rtPanel Hooks&#8217; to add extra functionality while developing theme.</p>\n<h3>Example &#8211; Adding Google-ad banner to rtPanel Child Theme Â above logo:</h3>\n<h3>Step 1:</h3>\n<p>At first we will create a custom field (textarea) in the custom theme option. So that when google ads script is added to that field, the google ads will appear before logo of the site. The custom field can be defined in the file &#8216;rtp-custom-theme-options.php&#8217; which is under the lib folder of Child theme of rtPanel. (learn more about &#8211; <a title=\"Custom Theme Options in rtPanel\" href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/custom-theme-options-rtpanel-child-theme/\">custom theme options in rtPanel</a>)</p>\n<h3>Step 2:</h3>\n<p>Once textarea field is created, we will add the google ads script to this textarea. Now first we will create custom function as &#8220;rtp_google_ads&#8221; in the &#8216;function.php&#8217; which is present in the child theme folder. This is to display the google-ads.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">function rtp_google_ads(){\n    global $rtp_custom_theme_options;\n    echo $rtp_custom_theme_options[\'google_ads\'];\n}</code></pre>\n<p>So once function is created, we need to âhookâ the function to the &#8216;rtp_hook_before_logo&#8217; action hook so that Google ad will be displayed before the logo. So the code will be as below:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"no-highlight\">add_action(\'rtp_hook_before_logo\',\'rtp_google_ads\');</code></pre>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">After adding this code the google ads will be displayed before the logo. It is show in below screenshot.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://rtcamp.com/blog/roundup-4-portals-and-1-blog-launched-by-rtcamp-in-2010/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1914\"><img style=\' display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\'  class=\"size-large  aligncenter  wp-image-5050\" src=\"http://rtcamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/google-ads-600x226.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"226\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Step 3:</h3>\n<p>Once google ad is displayed we will add style it according. This can be done by adding CSS styling to the &#8216;style.php&#8217; file in the child theme folder.</p>\n<p>Isn&#8217;t it pretty easy to add our own functionality to the theme!!! <img src=\'http://rtcamp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\' alt=\':)\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </p>\n<p>This is just a small example to demonstrate how our &#8216;rtp_hook_before_logo&#8217; can be used. But there are many more things that can be achieved using this hook, as long as your creativity will not end. Some example usages are adding social networking icons, adding images, adding search textbox etc.</p>\n<p>Do let us know, your creative usages of rtPanel Hooks via comments.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rtpanel/~4/BsfmDiyjnlY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/add-google-ad-banner-above-logo-in-rtpanel/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"http://rtcamp.com/tutorials/add-google-ad-banner-above-logo-in-rtpanel/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"Hooks in rtPanel Child theme\";s:7:\"attribs\"